article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- — Keyshawn Hall and Amari Kelly had 13 points apiece in George Mason's 69-60 victory against Saint Bonaventure on Saturday. Hall also had eight rebounds for the Patriots (14-5, 3-3 Atlantic 10 Conference). Kelly had seven rebounds. Darius Maddox shot 4 for 10, including 2 for 6 from beyond the arc to finish with 10 points. The Bonnies (11-6, 2-3) were led in scoring by Chad Venning, who finished with 17 points and seven rebounds. Mika Adams-Woods added 14 points for Saint Bonaventure. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
